OL,3,CInternet companies could face huge
OL,4,Cfines over content glorifying terrorism
OL,6,FThe regulations apply to material
OL,7,Fshared online that directly or
OL,8,Findirectly advocates for the
OL,9,Fcommission of terrorism offences.
OL,11,FThis includes the glorification of
OL,12,Fterrorist acts, soliciting others to
OL,13,Fcontribute towards offences, or to
OL,14,Fdirectly participate or aid in the
OL,15,Factivities of terrorist groups.
OL,17,FAn Coimisiun will have the power to
OL,18,Fimpose administrative fines on hosting
OL,19,Fservice providers ` up to 4% of global
OL,20,Fturnover for infringements of the EU
OL,21,FTerrorism Content Online Regulation.
